<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="transactivation_domain_tad">Transactivation Domain, TAD</a> - A domain of a <a href="#transcription_factor_tf">transcription factor</a> that interacts with the <a href="#transcription">transcriptional</a> machinery, cofactors, and/or <a href="#chromatin">chromatin</a> modifying machinery (eukaryotes only) in order to facilitate formation of the <a href="#tight_junction">transcriptional initiation complex (TIC)</a>.